Be careful next time you order by phone. you might not get what you ordered.  I've eaten at Sage several times since I moved to this area not too long ago. And tonight, my wife and I were driving by it and decided to order pickup food. I got a vegetable pad thai with no tofu, and my wife got a vegetable red curry.  They took the normal time, handled my bag and I left. But by the time I got back home I noticed my pad thai had shrimps, which I didn't order and didn't want in my food, and no veggies :( Since it was the rush hour, I didn't want to spent another hour going there to get another dish, so I called and asked if they would give me some credits back for a future time (I like this place and I was willing to pardon their little mistake). But the person who answered the phone, said it was my mistake, and that I ordered shrimp pad thai. I told her that this was not the case (and my wife is a witness) and she insisted that it was my mistake. I started to fee very irritated as she keeps telling me that it was my mistake. I mean... shrims sound exactly like "vegetable". We even repeated the order 3 times! (They also misspelled my name! So go figured!)  Anyway, after she talked to the manager, she said that it was not possible to give me a refund or credit towards a future order, and that if I wanted a new dish I should go back there now. I insisted that this was not possible due to the rush hour, and that I would rather just throw away the shrimps and eat the pad thai as is and get a credit or discount in my next visit, which I believe it is really fair. Besides they charged me extra for those shrimps. After she refused I hang off the phone and threw away the shrimp. And now I'm having a little allergic reaction because of those shrimps. Very disappointed.  Sage... you lost me, my family and my friends as a client.  Be careful next time you order by phone. you might not get what you ordered.

So much better than most.  Thanks to my daughter’s desire to live on pad Thai, ive eaten at about 2 dozen Thai spots in NYC. There’s the great authentic spots in Queens, and past that, so many are mediocre. So many suck. Sage, however, is not one of those.  I had the green curry with tofu and vegetables. It was presented beautifully, was creamy, fragrant, and surprisingly spicy. It almost requires no rice at all to enjoy.  The big kid had a noodle soup with beef. The broth was delicious—not at all starchy—and it was full of fresh veggies.  The daughter got the kids’ menu pad Thai—only $5–and it was really very good. It was the best pad Thai I can remember trying in Brooklyn.  I’d put this spot high on your Thai list.

We planned a birthday brunch event at Sage, the space look great and we had dinner at the restaurant before so we were very excited about it. When I called to make the reservation the hostess confirmed it. I then called a week after to reconfirm and there was not record of my reservation being made. Anyway, we didn’t make a big deal but did want to make sure we spoke with a manager since we had a birthday cake and wanted to watch a football game. After speaking to a manager we thought all will go smooth the day of the event but unfortunately to our surprise it was a big disappointment. When we arrived for the reservation we sat down (party of 15 people), we had one server who was sweet but had no idea what was going on and was going extremely unorganized. The food was never served at the same time which made it super awkward because some people had food and others didn’t. To top that our drinks took a long time to make (we ordered mimosas which don’t usually take much time to make). Additionally the bartender had a terrible attitude when we asked her if she could help us with drinks. Terrible service overall. When we tried to ask for the manager he came by and said that he was busy and that he didn’t have time for us, he said he was busy and the kitchen was short staffed.  We felt super unwelcome and truly wish we had our event somewhere else. Furthermore, the game was never played because the manager and the bartender could not figure out the TVs, when we made the reservation we specially ask for the 1pm football game which they said they could show but to our unpleasant surprise they didn’t have the channel. Again we really wished that we had the event somewhere else. Lastly, the birthday cake was served, the server didn’t at all assist us with a tray or plates or silverware. We had to get up and grab them ourselves. It was a terrible birthday experience and very embarrassing that we invited Our closest friends there. It’s such a disappointment because Sage has a great space. The manager Woo at the end of the event said that he was sorry and that next time we go back he will provide us with a huge discount on our bill. Unfortunately we will not go back there again. My advise to management is to train your staff better and actually Value customers who choose your establishment as a space to host special occasions. It was my 35th birthday and I truly wish I chose a different venue as all was extremely disappointing.
